CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 17, reads: "Optomistic - There was nothing but optimism on the faces of New York Yankee stars pitcher Ralph Terry and outfielder Hector Lopez before the beginning of the World Series on Wednesday.  The smiles didn't hold up as the Yankees bowed in the opener. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: New York Yankees baseball players Ralph Terry and Hector Lopez on field at opening game of 1960 World Series, Forbes Field
